# Cursor Rules for YOLO Object Detection Robovision UI Project

## Project Context
This is a YOLO object detection web application that we're redesigning with a futuristic robovision aesthetic using shadcn/ui components.

## MCP Configuration
The project has shadcn MCP server configured in `.vscode/settings.json` for AI assistance with shadcn/ui components.

## Tech Stack
- React 18 with Vite
- Tailwind CSS v4
- shadcn/ui components
- Framer Motion for animations
- ONNX Runtime Web for ML inference

## Design Goals
- Futuristic robovision aesthetic
- Holographic HUD interface
- Glowing elements and transparency
- Sci-fi heads-up display style
- Maintain all existing functionality

## Available Components
- Button, Select, Card, Badge, Progress
- Separator, Tooltip, Input, Label
- All shadcn/ui components are available

## Code Style
- Use shadcn/ui components when possible
- Maintain dark theme
- Add futuristic styling with glowing effects
- Use Framer Motion for smooth animations
- Preserve existing functionality completely

## File Structure
- `src/components/ui/` - shadcn/ui components
- `src/lib/utils.js` - Utility functions
- `src/assets/App.css` - Main styles
- `components.json` - shadcn configuration


